      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a deeply complex concept, and its danger level depends entirely on its manifestation. When it fosters shared identity, culture, and civic responsibility, it can be a powerful force for social cohesion and collective action. However, when nationalism devolves into chauvinism or xenophobia, it becomes an inherently dangerous ideology that justifies exclusion and conflict. Therefore, it is less an inherent good or evil and more a potent tool whose ethical use determines its impact.",
